1
00:00:05,776 --> 00:00:13,100
Once, rather enigmatically,
in Vṛndāvan, Śrīla Gurudev said to me,

2
00:00:14,162 --> 00:00:18,311
“If Kṛṣṇa doesn’t want 
to reveal himself to someone,

3
00:00:18,494 --> 00:00:20,306
then why should I?”

4
00:00:20,306 --> 00:00:22,555
[In Sync with Divinity]

5
00:00:22,772 --> 00:00:25,561
And that was
a peculiar statement,

6
00:00:25,561 --> 00:00:29,822
coming from someone who’s connecting 
so many people with Kṛṣṇa.

7
00:00:29,822 --> 00:00:32,021
But he was saying it
from another point of view.

8
00:00:32,021 --> 00:00:35,410
He was addressing that what 
needs to be understood

9
00:00:35,410 --> 00:00:40,962
is that Kṛṣṇa’s divine will 
has to be in the background.

10
00:00:40,962 --> 00:00:43,044
This is what
is most important,

11
00:00:43,044 --> 00:00:47,743
is that it is the will of Kṛṣṇa,
to reveal himself to someone;

12
00:00:47,743 --> 00:00:54,759
it’s Kṛṣṇa’s will 
to make Himself known to someone.

13
00:00:54,759 --> 00:00:58,425
And that means to the degree,
through a particular agency,

14
00:00:58,425 --> 00:01:00,566
all the different things
that we may consider:

15
00:01:00,566 --> 00:01:05,549
in the background, it
has to be Kṛṣṇa’s will.

16
00:01:06,026 --> 00:01:13,610
And we’re trying to sync our will
with the will of Kṛṣṇa.

17
00:01:18,926 --> 00:01:23,797
So, in a basic understanding,
Śrīla Guru Mahārāj himself says—

18
00:01:23,797 --> 00:01:28,765
when he was preaching once,
some man said to him,

19
00:01:28,765 --> 00:01:35,087
“If the infinite can be known
by the finite, it’s not infinite.”

20
00:01:35,087 --> 00:01:37,682
And Guru Mahārāj
responded by saying,

21
00:01:37,682 --> 00:01:43,412
“If the Infinite cannot make Himself known
to the finite, He's not infinite.”

22
00:01:43,412 --> 00:01:47,468
And therein lies our prospect
back to the will of Kṛṣṇa.

23
00:01:47,468 --> 00:01:52,345
If the Infinite wants
to make Himself known to the finite,

24
00:01:52,345 --> 00:01:54,288
not only will it happen,

25
00:01:54,288 --> 00:01:58,969
but nothing can obstruct
that divine flow—

26
00:01:58,969 --> 00:02:03,969
not any perceived lack of qualification
on the receiver,

27
00:02:03,969 --> 00:02:06,899
or any opaque intermediary;

28
00:02:06,899 --> 00:02:08,961
if it’s Kṛṣṇa’s will 
to reveal Himself,

29
00:02:08,961 --> 00:02:10,452
it will happen.

